TL;DR : Why would a doc prescribe Zoloft for ADHD?

&amp;#x200B;

I was recently officially diagnosed with ADHD, anxiety, ocd, and 'some' possible bipolar symptoms. My main issues are constantly having racing thoughts, putting things in different spots until it feels 'right', touching things over and over with both hands until it feels 'balanced', weird breathing patterns and constantly confirming my throat is clear, lack of focus/hard time staying focused, inability to sit still without feeling like I should be doing something, and pretty bad panic attacks when I leave my 'safe space' (home). Those would be the major things.
